---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Starling AIX | Mach 1 Business — Free AI Guide" description="Download Mach 1 Business free — the architecture guide for AI-native organizations. Includes the complete UCA Standard and Summon Starling appendix.">
<Nav currentPage="guide" />
<main>

<!-- ===== HERO ===== -->
<section class="guide-hero" id="hero">
    <div class="guide-hero__bg">
        <canvas id="heroCanvas"></canvas>
    </div>
    <div class="guide-hero__inner">
        <div class="guide-hero__text">
            <div class="guide-hero__badge">
                <span class="guide-hero__badge-dot"></span>
                Free eBook
            </div>
            <h1 class="guide-hero__title"><strong>The AI-native enterprise is here.</strong><br>Are you ready for it?</h1>
            <p class="guide-hero__subtitle">AI has arrived — it is now squarely in work.</p>
            <p class="guide-hero__desc">Claude connects to 50+ workplace tools. Agent teams run multi-step workflows. The outputs are Word docs, decks, and spreadsheets — not chat responses. The question isn't whether AI will change your organization. It's whether you've got the architecture to handle it.</p>
            <div class="guide-hero__cta">
                <div class="btn-group">
                    <a href="#download" class="btn btn--primary btn--large">
                        Get the Free eBook
                        <svg class="arrow" width="10" height="10" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M0.5 5.5h7"/><path d="M5.5 1.5l4 4-4 4"/></svg>
                    </a>
                    <a href="#toc" class="btn btn--secondary btn--large">Build Your Org Brain</a>
                </div>
                <p class="guide-hero__note">Includes the complete UCA Standard · Download below</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="guide-hero__visual">
            <div class="hero-term" id="heroTerminal">
                <div class="hero-term__bar">
                    <div class="hero-term__dots">
                        <span class="hero-term__dot" id="htDot1"></span>
                        <span class="hero-term__dot" id="htDot2"></span>
                        <span class="hero-term__dot" id="htDot3"></span>
                    </div>
                    <span class="hero-term__bar-title">
                        <span class="hero-term__bar-status" id="htBarStatus"></span>
                        Summon Starling
                    </span>
                </div>
                <div class="hero-term__body">
                    <!-- Step 1: Upload with progress bar -->
                    <div class="hero-term__upload" id="htUpload">
                        <div class="hero-term__upload-icon">
                            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M12 10v6m0-6l-3 3m3-3l3 3M3.5 18.5l.7-2.8c.2-.8.3-1.2.5-1.5a2 2 0 01.8-.8c.3-.2.7-.2 1.5-.2h10c.8 0 1.2 0 1.5.2a2 2 0 01.8.8c.2.3.3.7.5 1.5l.7 2.8"/><rect x="2" y="18" width="20" height="4" rx="1"/></svg>
                        </div>
                        <div class="hero-term__upload-text">
                            <div class="hero-term__upload-name">Mach 1 Business.pdf</div>
                            <div class="hero-term__upload-size" id="htUploadStatus">iPub · 2.4 MB · Uploading...</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="hero-term__upload-check" id="htCheck">
                            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg>
                        </div>
                        <div class="hero-term__upload-progress" id="htProgress"></div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Step 2: Command -->
                    <div class="hero-term__cmd" id="htCmd">
                        <span class="hero-term__cmd-prompt">▸</span>
                        <span class="hero-term__cmd-text" id="htCmdText"></span>
                        <span class="hero-term__cmd-cursor" id="htCursor"></span>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Step 3: Resolution steps with progress bars + spinners -->
                    <div class="hero-term__steps">
                        <div class="hero-term__step" id="htStep1">
                            <div class="hero-term__step-icon hero-term__step-icon--uca">
                                UCA
                                <div class="hero-term__step-check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="hero-term__step-body">
                                <div class="hero-term__step-label">Loading Standard <span class="hero-term__counter" id="htCount1"></span></div>
                                <div class="hero-term__step-value">Universal Cognitive Architecture <strong>v1.0</strong></div>
                                <div class="hero-term__step-progress"><div class="hero-term__step-fill hero-term__step-fill--uca" id="htFill1"></div></div>
                                <span class="hero-term__step-tag">11 Cognates · 28 Constitutional</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="hero-term__step" id="htStep2">
                            <div class="hero-term__step-icon hero-term__step-icon--brain">
                                DLM
                                <div class="hero-term__step-check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="hero-term__step-body">
                                <div class="hero-term__step-label">Activating Domain Language Model <span class="hero-term__counter" id="htCount2"></span></div>
                                <div class="hero-term__step-value">Semantic addressing <strong>online</strong> · O(1) lookup ready</div>
                                <div class="hero-term__step-progress"><div class="hero-term__step-fill hero-term__step-fill--brain" id="htFill2"></div></div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="hero-term__step" id="htStep3">
                            <div class="hero-term__step-icon hero-term__step-icon--dlm">
                                SOS
                                <div class="hero-term__step-check"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M5 13l4 4L19 7"/></svg></div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="hero-term__step-body">
                                <div class="hero-term__step-label">Smart OS <span class="hero-term__counter" id="htCount3"></span></div>
                                <div class="hero-term__step-value">AI Chief of Staff <strong>activated</strong> · Org Brain initialized</div>
                                <div class="hero-term__step-progress"><div class="hero-term__step-fill hero-term__step-fill--dlm" id="htFill3"></div></div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Step 4: Result -->
                    <div class="hero-term__result" id="htResult">
                        <div class="hero-term__result-header">
                            <span class="hero-term__result-title">✦ Starling Active</span>
                            <span class="hero-term__result-status"><span class="hero-term__result-dot"></span>Online</span>
                        </div>
                        <p class="hero-term__result-desc">Organizational intelligence ready. Ask me anything about your business architecture.</p>
                        <div class="hero-term__result-tags">
                            <span class="hero-term__result-pill" id="htPill1">Sovereignty ✓</span>
                            <span class="hero-term__result-pill" id="htPill2">Addressable ✓</span>
                            <span class="hero-term__result-pill" id="htPill3">Stateless AI ✓</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <!-- Replay -->
                    <button class="hero-term__replay" id="htReplay">↻ Replay activation</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<hr class="glow-line">

<!-- ===== SECTION 2: THE REAL PROBLEM ===== -->
<section class="section section--gray" id="problem">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section__header reveal">
            <h2 class="section__h"><strong>The tools work.</strong> The architecture doesn't.</h2>
            <div class="section__header-right">
                <p class="body-lg">AI got good fast. Your organization didn't reorganize to match. That's where the failures come from — not the model, prompt, or vendor. The knowledge underneath isn't structured.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="problem__cards">
            <div class="problem-card reveal reveal-d1">
                <div class="problem-card__pulse problem-card__pulse--sov"></div>
                <div class="problem-card__icon problem-card__icon--sov">
                    <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M12 15v2m-6 4h12a2 2 0 002-2v-6a2 2 0 00-2-2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v6a2 2 0 002 2zm10-10V7a4 4 0 00-8 0v4h8z"/></svg>
                </div>
                <span class="problem-card__label">Sovereignty</span>
                <h3 class="problem-card__title">Who owns your knowledge?</h3>
                <p class="problem-card__desc">Every conversation with AI teaches the platform more about how your organization thinks. If that intelligence lives on their servers, under their governance, improving their model — you're building someone else's asset.</p>
                <div class="problem-card__visual">
                    <div class="data-stream data-stream--out" style="top:25%"></div>
                    <div class="data-stream data-stream--out" style="top:50%;animation-delay:1s"></div>
                    <div class="data-stream data-stream--out" style="top:75%;animation-delay:2s"></div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="problem-card reveal reveal-d2">
                <div class="problem-card__pulse problem-card__pulse--lock"></div>
                <div class="problem-card__icon problem-card__icon--lock">
                    <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"><path d="M13.828 10.172a4 4 0 00-5.656 0l-4 4a4 4 0 105.656 5.656l1.102-1.101m-.758-4.899a4 4 0 005.656 0l4-4a4 4 0 00-5.656-5.656l-1.1 1.1"/></svg>
                </div>
                <span class="problem-card__label">Lock-in</span>
                <h3 class="problem-card__title">The HAL Architecture</h3>
                <p class="problem-card__desc">Try switching AI vendors after a year of accumulated context. That's the trap. When the platform owns the memory, switching means starting from zero. The more you use it, the harder it is to leave.</p>
                <div class="lock-chain">
                    <div class="lock-chain__link"></div>
                    <div class="lock-chain__link"></div>
                    <div class="lock-chain__link"></div>
                    <div class="lock-chain__link"></div>
                    <div class="lock-chain__link"></div>
                    <div class="lock-chain__link"></div>
                    <div class="lock-chain__link"></div>
                    <div class="lock-chain__link"></div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== SECTION 3: COGNITIVE DESIGN SOLUTION ===== -->
<section class="section section--white" id="solution">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section__header reveal">
            <h2 class="section__h"><strong>Search vs. Address.</strong> Every AI system today searches. That's the problem.</h2>
            <div class="section__header-right">
                <p class="body-lg">Search burns tokens re-discovering context you already have. Addressing eliminates the cost entirely. This is the shift from O(n) to O(1).</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="solution-toggle reveal reveal-d1">
            <div class="solution-toggle__bar" id="solToggleBar">
                <div class="solution-toggle__pill" id="solPill"></div>
                <button class="solution-toggle__btn is-active" data-panel="search">Current State</button>
                <button class="solution-toggle__btn" data-panel="address">Cognitive Architecture</button>
                <button class="solution-toggle__btn" data-panel="compare">Compare</button>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="solution-panels reveal reveal-d2" id="solPanels">
            <!-- Search panel -->
            <div class="solution-panel is-active" id="panel-search">
                <div class="solution-card">
                    <div class="sol-search__inner">
                        <div class="sol-search__label">
                            <span class="sol-search__label-dot"></span>
                            Search
                        </div>
                        <div class="sol-search__grid">
                            <div class="search-item" data-idx="0"><div class="search-item__icon search-item__icon--scatter">📂</div><div class="search-item__text"><strong>Scattered data</strong> across platforms — no single source of truth</div></div>
                            <div class="search-item" data-idx="1"><div class="search-item__icon search-item__icon--tangle">🔗</div><div class="search-item__text"><strong>Tangled connections,</strong> exponential complexity as you scale</div></div>
                            <div class="search-item" data-idx="2"><div class="search-item__icon search-item__icon--burn">🔥</div><div class="search-item__text"><strong>Every query burns tokens</strong> re-discovering context you already have</div></div>
                            <div class="search-item" data-idx="3"><div class="search-item__icon search-item__icon--wall">🧱</div><div class="search-item__text"><strong>RAG hits a wall</strong> at enterprise volume — retrieval degrades</div></div>
                            <div class="search-item" data-idx="4"><div class="search-item__icon search-item__icon--cost">📈</div><div class="search-item__text"><strong>Token cost scales</strong> with organizational size — no ceiling</div></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="sol-search__counter">
                        <span class="sol-search__counter-label">Est. token cost per query</span>
                        <span><span class="sol-search__counter-value" id="searchTokenCounter">0</span><span class="sol-search__counter-unit">tokens</span></span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="sol-graph">
                        <canvas id="searchViz"></canvas>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Address panel -->
            <div class="solution-panel" id="panel-address">
                <div class="solution-card">
                    <div class="sol-address__inner">
                        <div class="sol-address__label">
                            <span class="sol-address__label-dot"></span>
                            Address
                        </div>
                        <div class="sol-address__grid">
                            <div class="address-item" data-idx="0"><div class="address-item__icon">📍</div><div class="address-item__text"><strong>Organized knowledge</strong> in semantic coordinates — permanent addresses</div><span class="address-item__check"><svg width="10" height="10" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M2 5l2.5 2.5L8 3"/></svg></span></div>
                            <div class="address-item" data-idx="1"><div class="address-item__icon">⚡</div><div class="address-item__text"><strong>Instant retrieval</strong> — constant time regardless of scale</div><span class="address-item__check"><svg width="10" height="10" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M2 5l2.5 2.5L8 3"/></svg></span></div>
                            <div class="address-item" data-idx="2"><div class="address-item__icon">🎯</div><div class="address-item__text"><strong>O(1) lookup</strong> replaces O(n) search — no token burn</div><span class="address-item__check"><svg width="10" height="10" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M2 5l2.5 2.5L8 3"/></svg></span></div>
                            <div class="address-item" data-idx="3"><div class="address-item__icon">🧠</div><div class="address-item__text"><strong>The output is head code</strong> — canonical context your agents reference</div><span class="address-item__check"><svg width="10" height="10" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M2 5l2.5 2.5L8 3"/></svg></span></div>
                            <div class="address-item" data-idx="4"><div class="address-item__icon">🏗️</div><div class="address-item__text"><strong>Scales with structure,</strong> not volume — architecture over brute force</div><span class="address-item__check"><svg width="10" height="10" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M2 5l2.5 2.5L8 3"/></svg></span></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="sol-address__counter">
                        <span class="sol-address__counter-label">Lookup cost per query</span>
                        <span><span class="sol-address__counter-value" id="addressTokenCounter">0</span><span class="sol-address__counter-unit">tokens</span></span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="sol-graph">
                        <canvas id="addressViz"></canvas>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Compare panel -->
            <div class="solution-panel" id="panel-compare">
                <div class="solution-card">
                    <div class="sol-compare__inner">
                        <div class="sol-compare__metrics" id="compareMetrics">
                            <div class="sol-metric">
                                <div class="sol-metric__label">Cost per query</div>
                                <div class="sol-metric__row">
                                    <span class="sol-metric__val sol-metric__val--bad" data-target="4200" data-suffix="">0</span>
                                    <span class="sol-metric__vs">vs</span>
                                    <span class="sol-metric__val sol-metric__val--good" data-target="80" data-suffix="">0</span>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="sol-metric">
                                <div class="sol-metric__label">Latency</div>
                                <div class="sol-metric__row">
                                    <span class="sol-metric__val sol-metric__val--bad" data-target="3200" data-suffix="ms">0</span>
                                    <span class="sol-metric__vs">vs</span>
                                    <span class="sol-metric__val sol-metric__val--good" data-target="40" data-suffix="ms">0</span>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="sol-metric">
                                <div class="sol-metric__label">At 10x scale</div>
                                <div class="sol-metric__row">
                                    <span class="sol-metric__val sol-metric__val--bad" data-target="10" data-suffix="x">0</span>
                                    <span class="sol-metric__vs">vs</span>
                                    <span class="sol-metric__val sol-metric__val--good" data-target="1" data-suffix="x">0</span>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="sol-compare__graph">
                            <canvas id="compareViz"></canvas>
                            <div class="sol-compare__graph-legend">
                                <div class="sol-compare__legend-item"><span class="sol-compare__legend-dot" style="background:var(--accent-pink)"></span><span style="color:var(--accent-pink)">Search O(n)</span></div>
                                <div class="sol-compare__legend-item"><span class="sol-compare__legend-dot" style="background:#1a9e82"></span><span style="color:#1a9e82">Address O(1)</span></div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="sol-compare__split">
                            <div class="sol-compare__col sol-compare__col--search">
                                <div class="sol-compare__col-label sol-compare__col-label--search">
                                    <span class="sol-compare__col-label-dot" style="background:var(--accent-pink)"></span>
                                    Search — O(n)
                                </div>
                                <div class="sol-compare__item sol-compare__item--search" data-idx="0"><span class="sol-compare__item-icon search-item__icon--scatter">📂</span><span><strong>Scattered</strong> data across platforms</span></div>
                                <div class="sol-compare__item sol-compare__item--search" data-idx="1"><span class="sol-compare__item-icon search-item__icon--burn">🔥</span><span><strong>Burns tokens</strong> re-discovering context</span></div>
                                <div class="sol-compare__item sol-compare__item--search" data-idx="2"><span class="sol-compare__item-icon search-item__icon--cost">📈</span><span><strong>Cost scales</strong> with org size</span></div>
                            </div>
                            <div class="sol-compare__col sol-compare__col--address">
                                <div class="sol-compare__col-label sol-compare__col-label--address">
                                    <span class="sol-compare__col-label-dot" style="background:#1a9e82"></span>
                                    Address — O(1)
                                </div>
                                <div class="sol-compare__item sol-compare__item--address" data-idx="0"><span class="sol-compare__item-icon" style="background:rgba(54,209,183,0.1);color:#1a9e82">📍</span><span><strong>Organized</strong> in semantic coordinates</span></div>
                                <div class="sol-compare__item sol-compare__item--address" data-idx="1"><span class="sol-compare__item-icon" style="background:rgba(54,209,183,0.1);color:#1a9e82">⚡</span><span><strong>Instant retrieval</strong> at any scale</span></div>
                                <div class="sol-compare__item sol-compare__item--address" data-idx="2"><span class="sol-compare__item-icon" style="background:rgba(54,209,183,0.1);color:#1a9e82">🎯</span><span><strong>Constant cost</strong> — architecture wins</span></div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="sol-compare__verdict" id="compareVerdict">
                            <span class="sol-compare__verdict-icon">✦</span>
                            <span class="sol-compare__verdict-text">Cognitive Architecture eliminates 98% of token cost at scale</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== SECTION 4: WHO THIS IS FOR ===== -->
<section class="section section--gray" id="audience">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section__header reveal">
            <h2 class="section__h"><strong>Leaders who want AI that compounds,</strong> remembers, and delivers.</h2>
            <div class="section__header-right">
                <p class="body-lg">You're ready to get serious about AI implementation. But you're watching platforms rise and fall, vendors pivot overnight. You need architecture that outlasts the tools.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="audience__cards">
            <div class="audience-card reveal reveal-d1">
                <span class="audience-card__num">01</span>
                <div class="audience-card__icon audience-card__icon--deploy">🚀</div>
                <h3 class="audience-card__title">You've deployed AI and still get generic outputs.</h3>
                <p class="audience-card__desc">You've trained models on company knowledge. Built custom GPTs. Deployed agents that execute tasks but don't understand your business. Different teams re-teach the same context to different tools.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="audience-card reveal reveal-d2">
                <span class="audience-card__num">02</span>
                <div class="audience-card__icon audience-card__icon--domain">🧠</div>
                <h3 class="audience-card__title">You need AI that knows your domain.</h3>
                <p class="audience-card__desc">Not a search engine with memory. Not an autonomous model. A productivity booster that compounds your knowledge — where every session builds on the last, and the intelligence belongs to you.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="audience-card reveal reveal-d3">
                <span class="audience-card__num">03</span>
                <div class="audience-card__icon audience-card__icon--arch">🏗️</div>
                <h3 class="audience-card__title">You need architecture, not another tool.</h3>
                <p class="audience-card__desc">You don't need a technical background to realize this. You need a framework that makes your AI smarter every day — not just today's shiny interface that's tomorrow's technical debt.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== SECTION 5: WHAT YOU GET (Book TOC) ===== -->
<section class="section section--white" id="toc">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section__header reveal">
            <h2 class="section__h"><strong>Mach 1 Business.</strong> The architecture guide for AI-native organizations.</h2>
            <div class="section__header-right">
                <p class="body-lg">This book names the forces breaking enterprise AI, introduces the Domain Language Model, and includes the complete Universal Cognitive Architecture Standard as a working appendix. It's also a dataset — load it into your AI and summon Starling.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="toc-mockup reveal reveal-d1">
            <div class="toc-mockup__bar">
                <div class="toc-mockup__dots">
                    <span class="toc-mockup__dot"></span>
                    <span class="toc-mockup__dot"></span>
                    <span class="toc-mockup__dot"></span>
                </div>
                <span class="toc-mockup__title">Table of Contents</span>
            </div>
            <div class="toc-mockup__body">
                <div class="toc-section" data-toc="p1">
                    <div class="toc-section__header">
                        <div class="toc-section__icon toc-section__icon--p1">I</div>
                        <div class="toc-section__info">
                            <span class="toc-section__label">Part I — The Problem</span>
                            <span class="toc-section__name">Why Enterprise AI Fails</span>
                        </div>
                        <svg class="toc-section__chevron" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="currentColor"><path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M5.293 7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0L10 10.586l3.293-3.293a1 1 0 111.414 1.414l-4 4a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 010-1.414z"/></svg>
                    </div>
                    <div class="toc-section__body">
                        <p class="toc-section__content">Business has never had canon. The NL/JSON handoff point. Why 95% of enterprise AI pilots fail — and why the problem is architecture, not intelligence.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="toc-section" data-toc="p2">
                    <div class="toc-section__header">
                        <div class="toc-section__icon toc-section__icon--p2">II</div>
                        <div class="toc-section__info">
                            <span class="toc-section__label">Part II — The Architecture</span>
